The article is a transcript of a speech given by President Joe Biden at Ignite Glass Studios in Chicago, Illinois. The President thanked the Governor of Illinois, JB Pritzker, and expressed gratitude for the support received in the recent elections. He highlighted the victories of Democratic candidates in various states and emphasized the progress made in areas such as infrastructure, healthcare, job creation, and climate change. The President also spoke about the importance of protecting democracy and unity in the country, and criticized the actions and rhetoric of former President Donald Trump. He called on Americans to come together and work towards a brighter future for the United States.